The quarantine site for the South Africans returning from Wuhan is being prepared in Limpopo. Courtesy #DStv403 * Weekend-In-One articles examine the top stories of the week from all the angles you may have missed. Watch Week-in-One all weekend on DStv403. LIMPOPO - It is still a waiting game for the South Africans who were trapped in Wuhan, China, and for their families. The test results revealing whether they have been infected by COVID-19 were released on Thursday. The test results indicated the group has not been infected with the virus. READ: Food you need to buy if you are quarantined during the coronavirus outbreak The group has been placed in quarantine for 21 days at The Ranch Resort. "We continue to keep them in quarantine for the prescribed period and will thereafter initiate the process of reunifying them with the community," said Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize. Mkhize urged people to stay away from the venue. The number of confirmed cases of coronavirus has risen to 202 through the week. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.